SETTING JENKINS ON LOCAL:

=>INSTALL JENKINS LTS FOR WINDOWS ON LOCAL PC FROM:    https://www.jenkins.io/download/
=> While installing on Local , we will get below 2 options
      -> USE LOCAL SYSTEM: FOR ENTIRE PC(WE CAN SELECT THIS)
	  -> USE LOACL USER: IF YOUR LAPTOP HAS MANY PROFILES
=> JENKINS WILL SUPPORT ONLY JAVA 17 or JAVA 21, so we will need those version jdk for that
=> we do not need to set path for jenkins on local
=> we can run below command to check if jenkins is installed.
     > sc query jenkins
=> we can now open jenkins terminal depending on the port configured while installation
URL ON THIS PC: http://localhost:9000/login?from=%2F

=> It will ask for initial password while hitting above url
=> we will find the password here : C:\ProgramData\Jenkins\.jenkins\secrets\initialAdminPassword

=> Jenkins by default creates the logs folder in:C:\ProgramData\Jenkins\.jenkins\secrets\initialAdminPassword

=> if we want to change it:
    > click windows+R
	> type services.msc
	> stop jenkins service
	> copy all content from C:\ProgramData\Jenkins\
	> paste it inside desired folder , in this pc i have pasted in=>"C:\Users\ashut\Desktop\Tools\Jenkins\jenkins_home\.jenkins"
	
	> open enviroment variable , create a new variable name "JENKINS_HOME": paste the path=> "C:\Users\ashut\Desktop\Tools\Jenkins\jenkins_home\.jenkins"
	
	> Now we need point jenkins service to above new path
	> stop the service by command: > sc stop jenkins
	
	> point jenkins to the new path by command: > setx JENKINS_HOME "C:\Users\ashut\Desktop\Tools\Jenkins\jenkins_home\.jenkins" /M
	
NOW THE INSTALLION IS COMPLETE, BASIC JENKINS COMMANDS:

> sc start jekins(Start jenkins)
> sc stop jenkins (Stop jenkins)
> sc query jenkins (checking status of jenkins service)



# Update packages
sudo yum update -y

# Install Java (for Jenkins)
sudo dnf install java-11-amazon-corretto -y

# Installation of jenkins
>sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
>sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io.key
>sudo yum install jenkins -y

# Start Jenkins
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
sudo systemctl start jenkins

> sudo find / -name jenkins.war 2>/dev/null
> java -jar /usr/share/java/jenkins.war
>nohup java -jar /usr/share/java/jenkins.war &

PATH OF JENKINS IN MY AWS: /usr/share/java/jenkins.war

